# LWC / Aura

- Must pass `npm run lint` (`@salesforce/eslint-config-lwc`). ES modules, camelCase.
- Use `@wire` for reactive data; handle loading and error states explicitly.
- User-facing text comes from Custom Labels, not string literals — Aura and LWC
  can't reference Apex constants:
  - LWC: `import LABEL from "@salesforce/label/c.LEI_ClubMembership_..."`
  - Aura: `$A.get("$Label.c.LEI_ClubMembership_...")`
- Use SLDS. Check accessibility: labelled inputs, keyboard navigation, semantic markup.
- No hardcoded IDs, org URLs, or secrets in JS. Sanitize user-supplied content
  before rendering.
- New or changed components ship Jest specs (`npm run test:unit`).
